 million against their earnings.
 In accounting sense, consequently their GEICO goodwill will disappear gradually
 in even-sized bites.
 But the economic goodwill they have purchased at GEICO will not decline
 in the same measured way.
 In fact, Buffett's best guess is that the economic goodwill assignable
 to GEICO will not decline at all, but rather will increase - and probably
