 board should be small in size and composed mostly of outside directors.
 The strongest weapon a director can wield in these situations remains his
 or her threat to resign.
\end_layout

\begin_layout Itemize
All these situations do share a common characteristic: the terrible manager
 is a lot easier to confront or remove than the mediocre manager.
 A chief problem in all governance structures, Buffett emphasizes, is that
